<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282620>
    bibo:endPage "78" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "66" ;
    bibo:volume "3518" ;
    dc:creator "Rivero-Blanco, Carlos; Schargel, Walter E." ;
    dc:date "2012" ;
    dc:title "A strikingly polychromatic new species of Gonatodes (Squamata: Sphaerodactylidae) from northern Venezuela" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282622>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282623>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282624>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282625>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282626> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282622>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Adult male (top, holotype, MHNLS 20780) and adult female (bottom, UTA 60126) of Gonatodes rozei sp. nov. in life." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282622/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282623>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Scalation pattern in the gular area of Gonatodes rozei sp. nov. (left; illustration based on MHNLS 5532 from Valle de Guanape, Anzoátegui, Venezuela) and the falconensis complex (right; illustration based on specimen of G. taniae, TCWC 59378, from Rancho Grande, Aragua, Venezuela)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282623/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282624>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. The four different male color morphs in Gonatodes rozei sp. nov., I-IV, arranged from top to bottom. Illustration by Emil Bröckl." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282624/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282625>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. A pair of Gonatodes rozei sp. nov. copulating in captivity." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282625/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.282626>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Map of north central Venezuela showing the collecting localities of the specimens examined of Gonatodes rozei sp. nov.. The holotype is indicated by the star and all other localities by dots. The whole type series was collected within Guatopo National Park, which is delimited by a dashed line. The other three national parks are Waraira Repano (top), Macarao (left) and Laguna de Tacarigua (right)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/282626/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

